In England, in the seven days to 20 February, there were 66,612 new confirmed cases (118.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 77,944 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 15% (11,332 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 25 February is 3,639,352 (6,465.7 cases per 100,000 population).
